Procol Harum are a British rock band, formed in 1967, who contributed to the development of progressive rock, and by extension, symphonic rock. Their best known recording is their 1967 single "A Whiter Shade of Pale". Although noted for its baroque and classical influence, Procol Harum's music also embraces the blues, R&B and soul. <a href="
